  "response": "A diamond is a precious gemstone made entirely of carbon atoms arranged in a very strong, tetrahedral crystal structure. They are formed deep within the Earth's mantle under high temperature and pressure conditions, typically at depths of 140-190 kilometers. Diamonds are renowned for their:\n\n1. Hardness: They are the hardest natural material known\n2. Brilliance: They have exceptional ability to reflect and refract light\n3. Rarity: Natural diamonds are scarce and valuable\n4. Uses: Jewelry, industrial cutting tools, scientific equipment\n5. Typically colorless, but can also occur in various colors like yellow, blue, and pink\n\nDiamonds are usually mined from volcanic rock formations called kimberlites and are valued based on the \"4 Cs\": cut, clarity, color, and carat weight.",
